## Overview
Design and implement the command-line argument parsing for the Glow markdown reader using the clap crate. This establishes the foundation for all user interaction with the CLI.

## Requirements

### Positional Arguments
- `FILE` - Optional markdown file path to display
- Support for stdin input via `-` or piped content

### Flags and Options
- `-p, --pager` - Force pager mode (default when stdout is TTY)
- `-s, --style <STYLE>` - Glamour style (dark, light, dracula, etc.)
- `-w, --width <WIDTH>` - Word wrap width (default: terminal width)
- `-l, --local` - Show local files only (file browser mode)
- `--config <PATH>` - Custom config file path

### Feature-Gated Options
- `--github <REPO>` - Fetch README from GitHub repo (requires github feature)
- `--stash` - Open document stash (requires stash feature)

### Subcommands
- `glow` - Default, render markdown
- `glow config` - Show/edit configuration
- `glow stash` - Manage stashed documents (feature-gated)

## Implementation Details
```rust
use clap::{Parser, Subcommand, ValueEnum};

#[derive(Parser)]
#[command(name = "glow")]
#[command(about = "Render markdown in the terminal")]
pub struct Cli {
    /// Markdown file to display
    pub file: Option<PathBuf>,

    /// Force pager mode
    #[arg(short, long)]
    pub pager: bool,

    /// Rendering style
    #[arg(short, long, default_value = "auto")]
    pub style: Style,

    // ... additional fields
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All arguments parse correctly with helpful error messages
